<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<xsl:stylesheet xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xmlns:dita="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" version="2.0" exclude-result-prefixes="dita">

	<dita:topic xmlns="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="UK14_Precedents_table_pgwide">
    <title>(UK14) <sourcexml>table[@pgwide]</sourcexml> check attribute value
            <lnpid>id-UK14-30231</lnpid></title>
    <body>
        <section>
            <p>This is a rule specific to UK14 Precedents regarding
                    <sourcexml>table[@pgwide]</sourcexml>.</p>
            <p><sourcexml>table</sourcexml> converts as described in <xref href="../../common_newest/Rosetta_table-LxAdv-table.dita">"<sourcexml>table</sourcexml> to <targetxml>table</targetxml>
                    (id-CCCC-10475)"</xref>.</p>
            <p>UK14 additional rule based on <sourcexml>@pgwide</sourcexml> value: <ul>
                    <li>If <sourcexml>@pgwide</sourcexml> value is <sourcexml>"0"</sourcexml> (zero)
                        or <sourcexml>"1"</sourcexml> then map to target as usual, i.e. becomes
                            <targetxml>@pgwide="0"</targetxml> or
                        <targetxml>@pgwide="1"</targetxml>.</li>
                    <li>If value is anything else, e.g. <sourcexml>"true"</sourcexml> or
                            <sourcexml>"false"</sourcexml>, then suppress
                            <sourcexml>@pgwide</sourcexml>, do not map to target.</li>
                </ul></p>
            <pre>
        <b>EXAMPLE 1: <sourcexml>@pgwide="0"</sourcexml> or <sourcexml>@pgwide="1"</sourcexml>, convert</b>
            
<b><i>Source XML</i></b>

&lt;table frame="none" pgwide="0"&gt;
    &lt;!-- contents of table --&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table frame="none" pgwide="1"&gt;
    &lt;!-- contents of table --&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
 
<b><i>Target XML</i></b>

&lt;table frame="none" pgwide="0"&gt;
    &lt;!-- contents of table --&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table frame="none" pgwide="1"&gt;
    &lt;!-- contents of table --&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

                </pre>
            <pre>
        <b>EXAMPLE 2: <sourcexml>@pgwide</sourcexml> is any other value, suppress</b>
            
<b><i>Source XML</i></b>

&lt;table frame="none" pgwide="true"&gt;
    &lt;!-- contents of table --&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
 
<b><i>Target XML</i></b>

&lt;table frame="none"&gt;
    &lt;!-- contents of table --&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

                </pre>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Changes</title>
            <p>2016-12-13: <ph id="change_20161213_jm">Modified rule to base
                        <sourcexml>@pgwide</sourcexml> conversion on the attribute's value.
                    Attribute is mapped to target when value is <sourcexml>"0"</sourcexml> or
                        <sourcexml>"1"</sourcexml>. Otherwise suppressed. Previously, this rule
                    simply suppressed <sourcexml>@pgwide</sourcexml> while rosetta markup was in
                    transition.</ph></p>
            <p>2016-10-05: <ph id="change_20161005_jm">Created.</ph></p>
        </section>
    </body>
	</dita:topic>

